### Phase 3: ADR-18 Critical Audit (REVISED)

**Original (Terminal grep):**
```bash
grep -i "thought.*detect" GSA-v7.2-rev9.user.js  # ❌
```

**Revised (Browser DevTools):**

**Method 1: Text Editor Search**
```javascript
// In VS Code / text editor:
// Find (Ctrl+F) with regex enabled:

// Check 1: No thought detection
// Search: (thought.*detect|querySelector.*thought|aria.*thought)
// Expected: 0 matches

// Check 2: No auto clipboard
// Search: (setInterval.*clipboard|while.*clipboard)
// Expected: 0 matches

// Check 3: Single clipboard read
// Search: navigator\.clipboard\.readText
// Expected: 1 match (in Unit B click handler)

// Check 4: No thought UI manipulation
// Search: (querySelector.*viewer|click.*thought|expand.*thought)
// Expected: 0 matches
```

**Method 2: Runtime Validation (F12 Console)**
```javascript
// After script loads in Google AI Studio:
// Open F12 Console and run:

// Test: Verify UnitB is passive (no auto-actions)
console.log("Testing UnitB passivity...");

// 1. Check clipboard read only happens on click
let clipboardReadCount = 0;
const originalRead = navigator.clipboard.readText;
navigator.clipboard.readText = async function() {
  clipboardReadCount++;
  console.log("📋 Clipboard read triggered:", clipboardReadCount);
  return originalRead.call(navigator.clipboard);
};

// 2. Wait 5 seconds - should be 0 reads
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("Auto-read check:", clipboardReadCount === 0 ? "✅ PASS" : "❌ FAIL");
}, 5000);

// 3. Click VERDER button manually
// Then check: clipboardReadCount should be 1

// Expected console output:
// Auto-read check: ✅ PASS
// (after manual VERDER click): 📋 Clipboard read triggered: 1
```

**Gate:**
- [ ] All 4 text editor searches documented
- [ ] F12 runtime test passes (0 auto-reads)
- [ ] Manual VERDER click triggers exactly 1 read

